Chickadees and perhaps other small birds will roost under dead leaves
still hanging on trees.  Some oak trees hang on to their dead leaves
into the winter.  Chickadees will roost under clumps of these hanging
down.   Their body temperature is so high that they create a
mini-environment in a small space.    Other small creatures also have
this ability.  One time while we were living in St. Louis one of our
domestic rabbits had gotten loose and produced babies in a shallow
nest she built under the back porch.  One night it was going to go
down to -15 and I knew that mother rabbits do not stay in the nest
with their babies.  I also knew that if I moved them she might reject
them but I decided to risk bringing them in the house because i was
sure they were going to freeze to death anyway.  when I pulled aside
the fur ball they were covered in and stuck my hand in to retrieve the
babies, I was amazed at how hot it was inside the nest.  I covered
them back uyp and left them.  They were fine.  Nature has her ways.

